# Copycat Controller is Live!
@sportstensor・41 

## What is the Copycat Controller (CC)?
It's a function that helps us find similar miner outputs across different UIDs and punish them if they have been flagged repeatedly by the CC.
The kind of activity that will be punished includes:
- Miners using the same model across different UIDs
- Miners who are only seeking the local maxima in the gaussian filter (only making predictions where win probability fetches the highest scores)
- Relay miners

## Why is CC important?
UID-squatting is a big problem in Bittensor and not just for this subnet. It disproportionately distributes incentives to miners who register multiple UIDs yet provide no additional value. In our subnet, particularly competitive UID-squatters will use their unfairly earnt incentives to mass reg UIDs to kill competition. This is against decentralization, Sportstensor's values and the ethos of Bittensor.

CC (along with new hyperparameters) will make it redundant to register multiple UIDs. We believe this will solve the deregistration problem a lot of miners have been facing recently, while giving new miners space to meet the threshold of predictions.

This is a necessary step towards our ultimate goal of providing real world clients with **actionable and reliable edge** in the sports prediction markets. In saying that, the CC is not perfect and we will be adjusting thresholds and parameters to ensure fairness while disincentivizing miners only looking to extract value from the network.

A quick shout out to the Taoshi (SN8) team for contributing their expertise to our Copycat Controller.

## How does it work?
The CC builds a matrix of suspicious predictions amongst all miner combinations and then analyzes those predictions for both exact duplicates as well as predictions varying by our threshold.

If `15` (current constant) or more matches are found to have **exact duplicates** between `2` miners, those `2` miners will be flagged and penalized to `0`.

If `15` (current constant) or more matches **in a row** are found to have predictions **varying by less than or equal to our variance threshold** between `2` miners, those `2` miners will be flagged and penalized to `0`.

The constants are subject to change at our discretion as we continue to analyze the predictions of miners on the subnet.

## What happens next?
The CC is in full effect. It has begun retroactively scanning and flagging miner activity so over the next few days we should see a change in the distribution curve. **We have reduced the adjustment alpha to dissuade mass registrations during this time.**

## Lay bets. What are they and why are we addressing them?
@sportstensor・41 

We have noticed that some creative miners have found a way to earn a higher score with the same prediction by predicting **a team to lose rather than win**. An example of this is a miner will choose Team A with a win probability of **0.1** (10%) as their prediction - effectively saying that Team B is the actual winner.

Now if winning an 'inverse prediction' gives you a higher score than usual, *losing the same will punish you more aswell*. It is still scored fairly but considered a gamble.

In the real world this is called a *lay bet* and is something you can legally do on exchanges, even as a betting strategy. However, the results of a lay bet from a back (normal) bet would be same. Which is why we are working on the scoring mechanism as we speak to make sure that is reflected on our subnet as well.
